  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is power flushing?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Power flushing is a professional cleaning process that pumps high-velocity water mixed with chemical cleaning agents through your central heating system at low pressure. It dislodges and removes sludge, magnetite, rust and debris from radiators, pipework and the boiler heat exchanger. The process typically takes 4 to 8 hours and is completed in a single visit." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How much does power flushing cost in Liverpool?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A power flush in Liverpool costs from £350 for a standard home with up to 10 radiators. Larger systems with 11 to 15 radiators cost from £450. The price includes all cleaning chemicals, a full inhibitor dose and a written system report. Call Ideal Plumbing Solutions on 07399 676656 for a fixed-price quote." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does a power flush take?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A power flush takes between 4 and 8 hours depending on system size and contamination level. A typical 3-bed Liverpool property takes around 6 hours. Small systems with up to 6 radiators take 3 to 4 hours. We always complete in a single visit with a morning start recommended." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How often should I power flush my central heating?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The Chartered Institute of Plumbing and Heating Engineering and the Power Flush Association both recommend power flushing every 5 to 7 years. Annual boiler servicing should include inhibitor level checks between flushes. If inhibitor levels drop, corrosion accelerates and systems may need flushing sooner." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can power flushing cause leaks?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Power flushing operates at low pressure around 2 bar and does not blast pipes. It can expose existing pinhole leaks in corroded radiators previously masked by debris. A qualified engineer will identify and address any leaks exposed during the flush and can often replace a faulty radiator on the same visit." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need a power flush before a new boiler in Liverpool?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, in most cases. Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal and Baxi all require a clean system as a warranty condition. Installing a new boiler on a contaminated system can void the manufacturer warranty and damage the new heat exchanger within months. Ideal Plumbing Solutions carries out the flush before the new boiler is connected to protect it from day one." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is power flushing suitable for all heating systems?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Power flushing is less effective on microbore systems which need a chemical cleanse first. Very old systems with hardened sludge flake may require powder flushing. Open-vented gravity-fed systems require different technique. We assess your system before recommending the right approach and will not carry out a flush we do not believe is right for your property." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What will power flushing not fix?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Power flushing will not fix broken valves, resolve pressure loss caused by leaks, remove limescale from heat exchangers, repair mechanical faults or seal existing leaks. It cleans the water circuit but does not fix mechanical components. We always carry out an honest assessment before starting." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I know if my Liverpool home needs a power flush?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The main signs are cold spots at the bottom of radiators, boiler making banging or kettling noises, the system taking much longer to warm up than it used to, black water when bleeding radiators and some radiators not heating at all. If you recognise two or more of these signs, call Ideal Plumbing Solutions on 07399 676656 for a free assessment." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are you Gas Safe registered?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Ideal Plumbing Solutions is Gas Safe registered. You can verify our registration at gassaferegister.co.uk. All our engineers are directly employed by us. We never use sub-contractors." }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

