        <p>The <a href="https://www.ciphe.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chartered Institute of Plumbing and Heating Engineering</a> and the <a href="https://www.powerflushassociation.com/faq.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Power Flush Association</a> both recommend this interval for a well-maintained system. Annual boiler servicing should include inhibitor level checks between flushes. If inhibitor levels are allowed to drop, corrosion accelerates and the system may need flushing sooner.</p>
